definitions.definition: A pavilion or portable lodge consisting of skins, canvas , or some strong cloth, stretched and sustained by poles, used for sheltering people from the weather.
examples: We were camping in a three-man tent .
We bought a new tent that can be put up in five seconds, but it took about twenty minutes to take it down and pack it away.

definitions.definition: ( archaic ) The representation of a tent used as a bearing .
( Scotland ) A portable pulpit set up outside to accommodate worshippers who cannot fit into a church.
A trouser tent ; a piece of fabric , etc. protruding outward like a tent.

definitions.definition: ( archaic , UK , Scotland , dialect ) Attention; regard, care.

definitions.definition: ( medicine ) A roll of lint or linen, or a conical or cylindrical piece of sponge or other absorbent, used chiefly to dilate a natural canal, to keep open the orifice of a wound, or to absorb discharges.
( medicine ) A probe for searching a wound.

definitions.definition: A kind of red wine of a deep red color, chiefly from Galicia or Malaga in Spain.
